    "plan_content": "Here's the complete plan for adding `next/geo`:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n### 5 files total (4 creates, 1 modify)\n\n**Step 1 — Core implementation:** `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts`\n- Pure TypeScript, zero external imports (unlike `user-agent.ts` which pulls in `ua-parser-js`)\n- Exports: `Geo` interface, `COUNTRY_NAMES` map (10 entries), `geoFromHeaders()`, `geo()`, `isInRegion()`, `geoDistance()`\n- `Headers.get()` returns `null`, so `?? undefined` throughout to satisfy strict TS\n- Vercel headers take priority; `cf-ipcountry` is fallback for `countryCode` only\n- `country` is derived by uppercasing `countryCode` and looking it up in `COUNTRY_NAMES`\n- Haversine formula with `atan2` for numerical stability; returns km as `number`\n\n**Step 2 — CJS entry point:** `packages/next/geo.js`\n- Mirrors `packages/next/server.js` exactly: builds a `geoExports` object, then sets both `module.exports` and individual `exports.X` named properties (supports both default + named imports)\n- Requires from `next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo` (the compiled output path)\n\n**Step 3 — Type definitions:** `packages/next/geo.d.ts`\n- Mirrors `packages/next/server.d.ts`: uses `export type { Geo }` + `export { geo, geoFromHeaders, isInRegion, geoDistance }` all from `next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo`\n\n**Step 4 — Register in `package.json`:** Insert `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` into the `files` array after `\"form.d.ts\"` (alphabetical: f < **g** < h)\n\n**Step 5 — Tests:** `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts`\n- Uses Jest (matches co-located test pattern: `request-cookies.test.ts`, `headers.test.ts`)\n- Covers: full Vercel headers extraction, missing headers → `undefined`, CF fallback, Vercel-over-CF priority, unknown country code, `isInRegion` case-insensitivity, `geoDistance` NY→London ≈ 5570 km (±50 km), zero distance for same point\n\n### Verification\n```bash\npnpm --filter=next types                        # fast type check (~10s)\npnpm test-unit .../geo.test.ts                  # run tests\npnpm --filter=next build                        # full compile to dist/\n```",
